# Vignette caching items
Meta/
doc/

# Regenerated by roxygen2() in CI (#53, #115): man pages, NAMESPACE, and the
# roxyglobals-managed R/globals.R are all documentation-process output, so the
# build regenerates them rather than tracking them. Every workflow that builds,
# installs, or checks the package runs `roxygen2::roxygenise()` first (which
# bootstraps a missing NAMESPACE). man/figures/ stays tracked because the
# package logo and other curated assets aren't roxygen output.
man/*.Rd
R/globals.R
.bin/

# Fitted-data artifacts regenerated on build by data-raw/fit_data.R (#64). The
# *_sim inputs (locations/observations/populations_sim) stay tracked; these
# four are derived from them and are large/version-fragile, so they are not.
data/fit_sim.rda
data/target_sim.rda
data/predict_sim.rda
data/latent_params_sim.rda
/doc/
/Meta/
